algorithm
Class MultiplePrintStream

java.lang.Object
  algorithm.MultiplePrintStream

public class MultiplePrintStream
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to copy one Printstream to multiple outputs. You find an example in the main-method which prints parallelto a file and the System.out PrintStream.
Note: You have to run the init-method before using a MultiplePrintStream.

Author:
chrissy

Field Detail

psArray

protected java.io.PrintStream[] psArray
This array contains all Printstreams. A "println()" call printed once for each PrintStream inside the array

standard

protected java.io.PrintStream standard
this is a standard PrintStream initialized with System.out.
An exceptions can be thrown by the initialization of all PrintStreams - ie. they are a file or something similar. Iff at least one PrintSream-Initialization failes all PrintStreams are redirected to this standard PrintStream

Method Detail

init

protected void init(int k)
This method initializes the inside PrintStream-Array psArray with k different Printstreams.
Each PrintStream is initialized by the standard PrintStream of the class.

Parameters:
k - number of different PrintStreams

setPrintStream

public boolean setPrintStream(int k,
                              java.io.PrintStream ps)
This method is used to delegate the PrintStream with index k to antoher Stream. For example you can delegate such a stream to a file or something else.
For more details of such a file delegation see the algorithm -method.

Parameters:
k - index of the PrintStream to set to ps
ps - PrintStream you set the kth PrintStream to
Returns:
a boolean that reports the success of this operation
